Articles.Content:
14 hours ago, Firefox101 said:

Any help?

As TheRagingIrishman already told you this kind of error usually occurs when you have at least one incompatible mod installed.

Upload the output log to a third party site like pastebin or dropbox and link it here. And please don't paste the content directly into the forum, it's not meant to display megabytes of text.
Welcome to the forum, @Firefox101! It looks like you are running the game with mods installed. Is that right? In that case I can move your question to the other part of the forum for modded installs.

I have the same problem. I submitted a zipped up set of logs to Support.

I have a fresh install of 1.3.0 and no mods*, on Windows 10-x64.

*gasp!

mono.dll caused an Access Violation (0xc0000005)


  in module mono.dll at 0023:1011a28a.

Error occurred at 2017-09-10_005542.
C:\Kerbal Space Program\KSP.exe, run by Unknown.
48% memory in use.
0 MB physical memory [0 MB free].
0 MB paging file [3169 MB free].
0 MB user address space [80 MB free].
Write to location 008cf000 caused an access violation.

 

In this Steam thread, somebody claimed that setting texture scale down helped.
Hi @dvp. Sorry to hear you're having problems. A stock install, you say? Interesting. Are you by any chance running the 32 bit version?

8 hours ago, Deddly said:

Hi @dvp. Sorry to hear you're having problems. A stock install, you say? Interesting. Are you by any chance running the 32 bit version?

Nope. KSP_x64.exe.

Crashes only seem to occur when I'm switching to or from the planet/tracking view. Some googling seems to indicate that it's a not-uncommon error with the Unity engine. A lot of hits around 2013. Nothing solid re: a fix.

Here's somebody with the same error playing Skylines.

Somebody probably needs to patch something, and it will be quietly fixed in 1.3.2 or somesuch. In the meantime, I'm going longer between crashes than I really ought to be in front of the computer, and autosave is doing its job, so I'm not delaying my Minmus expedition.
How much RAM do you have, @dvp?
